<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/355: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-22T20:00:00+01:00">November 22,
                                1932—8 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 8:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>47. From <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>. Referring to my
                        telegram No. 46, November 22, 6 p.m., it is proposed to call a meeting of
                        the Preparatory Commission about January 5th. It occurs to us that this
                        might be a few days early for American experts and we would appreciate your
                        ascertaining and cabling us what date prior to January 15th would be
                        satisfactory for experts meeting; also please confirm for communication to
                        president of Preparatory Commission that American members of Preparatory
                        Commission agree to inclusion of Chinese expert. [<persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>